lead_paragraph: The reigning Olympic champion Jenn Suhr broke her own women’s world indoor pole vault record by clearing 5.03 meters (16 feet 6 inches) at the Golden Eagle Invitational meet in Brockport, N.Y. Suhr broke the mark she established in 2013.
snippet: The reigning Olympic champion Jenn Suhr broke her own women’s world indoor pole vault record by clearing 5.03 meters (16 feet 6 inches) at the Golden Eagle Invitational meet in Brockport, N.Y. Suhr broke the mark she established in 2013.
abstract: Jenn Suhr wins women's indoor pole vault at Golden Eagle Invitational in Brockport, NY, clearing 5.03 meters and breaking her own record set in 2013.
